the Charter of the United Nations
Of particular relevance here is Article 19, of the UN’s Universal Declaration of Human Rights which states “Everyone has the right to freedom of opinion and expression; this right includes freedom to hold opinions without interference and to seek, receive and impart information and ideas through any media and regardless of frontiers.” [See further https://www.un.org/en/universal-declaration-human-rights/ ]
